nt ideas to pilot the affairs of the state. “Our governorship aspirants are a young crop of people. “I can tell you that in Edo 2020 election, PDP will produce a young governorship candidate,” Orbih said. He called on the electorate to make the right choice in the forthcoming governorship election by choosing a PDP candidate “because of the abysmal failure of the APC-led government in the state”. The party chairman urged people of Etsako Central to come together to work for the victory of the party at the election. “PDP remains the only organised party in Nigeria that knows how to resolve its crisis. “We are tired of the pains and disappointment we have found ourselves in the APC-led government in Edo. “I pray for peace and unity in the forthcoming election. “I want to assure you that this election will not be business as usual,” Orbih said. Vanguard The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Edo has adopted a no-zoning policy in picking the party’s governorship candidate for the state gubernatorial election in 2020. October 7, 2019 In "News" AHEAD the July 14, governorship election in Edo State, Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in the state has fixed February 25, for its governorship primaries. January 23, 2012 In "News" Chief Dan Orbih, Edo State Chairman of the People’s Democratic Party( PDP), has urged members of the party not to be deterred by those who decamped to the All Progressives Congress (APC). Orbih, who made the call at a rally in Owan West Local Government on Saturday, noted that those who… January 12, 2020 In "News"